== Usage ==

=== Template syntax ===

:<nowiki>{{TC stats table start|year=|basin=}}</nowiki>
::* ''year'' is the year this table is for.
::* ''basin'' is the oceanic basin this tables is for (i.e., "Atlantic hurricane"; see [[:Category:Tropical cyclones by basin]])

=== Construction of tropical cyclone tables ===

The overall way of constructing a tropical cyclones statistics table is given below.  Unless explicitly indicated otherwise, the templates are used in the order in which they are given.  The parameters for each template is described in its definition.

:<nowiki>{{TC stats table start|year=|basin=}}</nowiki>
::<nowiki>{{</nowiki>[[:template:TC stats cyclone|TC stats cyclone]]|cat=|name=|dates=|max-winds=|min-press=|ace=|mult-landfalls=<nowiki>}}</nowiki>
::<nowiki>{{</nowiki>[[:template:TC stats no landfall|TC stats no landfall]]<nowiki>}}</nowiki>
:::* Used when the storm has no landfalls.
::<nowiki>{{</nowiki>[[:template:TC stats first landfall|TC stats first landfall]]|where=|date=|winds=|cat=<nowiki>}}</nowiki>
:::* Used when the storm has at least one landfall.
::<nowiki>{{</nowiki>[[:template:TC stats impact|TC stats impact]]|damage=|deaths=|mult-landfalls=<nowiki>}}</nowiki>
::<nowiki>{{</nowiki>[[:template:TC stats next landfall|TC stats next landfall]]|where=|date=|winds=|cat=<nowiki>}}</nowiki>
:::* Used for a second landfall, and repeated for each subsequent landfall. 
::* Repeat the above indented templates once for each storm
:<nowiki>{{</nowiki>[[:template:TC stats table end|TC stats table end]]|num-cyclones=|dates=|max-winds=|min-press=|tot-ace=|num-landfalls=|tot-damage=|tot-deaths=<nowiki>}} </nowiki>

